      </ul>
    </div>

    <a name='usage'></a>
    <h2>Examples and usage</h2>
    <div class='section usage'>

      <h3>Setup</h3>
      <code>
    &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="jquery.1.4.2.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script type="text/javascript" src="jquery.busy.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
      </code>

      <h3>Default behaviour</h3>
      <div>
        <button class='example-default'>Click me!</button>
        <button class='example-default'>Click me!</button>
        <button class='example-default'>Click me!</button>
      </div>
      <code>
    jQuery('.example-default').click(function() {
      var that = jQuery(this).busy();

      setTimeout(function() {
        that.busy("hide");
      }, 2000);
    });
      </code>

      <h3>Positioning</h3>
      <button class='example-position'>Click me!</button>
      <code>
    jQuery('.example-position').click(function() {
      var that = jQuery(this).busy({ position : 'right', hide : false });

      setTimeout(function() {
        that.busy("hide");
      }, 2000);
    });
      </code>

      <h3>Repositioning</h3>
      <p>
      Since busy images are positioned absolutely changing page contents or dimensions when they are displayed may cause them to
      land in inappropriate places. The workaround for this is repositioning of busy images on such events. You can try this by
      changing the width of browser window. But still, animating content may be tricky...
      </p>
      <button class='example-reposition'>Click me!</button>
      <code>
    jQuery(window).resize(function() {
      jQuery().busy("reposition");
    });
      </code>

      <h3>Preloading the image (optional)</h3>
      <p>Preloading the image will prevent delay before showing it for the first time (when it is not cached yet).</p>
      <code>
    jQuery().busy("preload");
      </code>

      <h3>Changing defaults</h3>
      <code>
    jQuery().busy("defaults", { offset : 0, hide : false });
      </code>
    </div>

    <h2>Available options</h2>
    <div class='section available-options'>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <code>img</code>
